Creating the Dashboard Title and Slicers


Click on this icon located on the top left side of the page to download the document containing detailed color and dimensions information

Dashboard Title

1.    On the Power BI Desktop Home tab, select Text box

2.    Navigate to the following sections in the Visualizations field From bottom to top

a.    Switch Visual header to Off

b.    Switch Border to On (Default Color will be black)

c.    Switch Background to Off

d.    Switch Title to On

e.    Click on the Title drop-down and make adjustments as shown on the GIF below:

f.      Click on the General drop-down and adjust the dimensions as shown on the GIF below:


Slicers

1.    Select the slicer icon in the Visualizations field

2.    Select the County field by checking the corresponding box to add it to the slicer

3.    Change the slicer type to Drop-down

4.    Navigate to the following sections in the Format field From bottom to top

a.    Switch Visual header to Off

b.    Switch Border to On (Default Color will be black)

c.    Switch Background to On (Default Color will be white)

d.    Switch Title to Off

e.    Click on the Items drop-down and make the adjustments as shown on the GIF below:

(UPDATE: Use font family = Segoe UI for better visibility)

f.      Click on the Slicer header drop-down and make adjustments as shown on the GIF below:

g.    Click on the Selection controls drop-down a and make adjustments as shown on the GIF below:

h.    Click on the General drop-down and adjust the dimensions as shown on the GIF below:

5.    Duplicate the County slicer by selecting the slicer, right click, copy visual, then pasting it twice using Ctrl + V on your keyboard


Insurance Plan Slicer

1.    Click on the General drop-down and adjust the dimensions as shown on the GIF below:

2.    Remove County from the Values field and replace with Insurance Plan

(UPDATE: Use font family = Segoe UI for better visibility)

Year Slicer

1.    Click on the General drop-down and adjust the dimensions as shown on the GIF below:

2.    Remove County from the Values field and replace with Year

3.    Change the slicer type to Between

4.    Click on the Numeric inputs drop-down and make the following changes as shown on the GIF below:

(UPDATE: Use font family = Segoe UI for better visibility)
